[[Image:Bochum - Alleestraße - Westpark - Jahrhunderthalle (oT) 01 ies.ogv|thumb|300px|A car making a '''U-turn'''.]]

===Alternative forms===
* [[u-turn]]

===Etymology===
[[U]] + [[turn]], from the similarity to the shape of the letter ''U''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|literally|lang=en}} A [[turn]] in a [[vehicle]] carried out by driving in a [[semicircle]] in order to travel in the opposite direction.
# {{context|figuratively|lang=en}} A reversal of [[policy]]; a [[volte-face]], a [[backflip]]
#: ''The government have done a'' '''U-turn''' ''and are now supporting greater European integration instead of opposing it.''

====Usage notes====
* Often used in the phrases {{term||do a U-turn|lang=en}} or {{term||make a U-turn|lang=en}}.

====Synonyms====
* [[uey]] (''Australian & US, colloquial''), [[U-ie]] (''Australian & US, colloquial''), [[Uwey]] (''Australian & US, colloquial''),

